Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Pop the @panko breadcrumbs{10%g} into a #medium bowl{}. Add the @water{2%tbsp} and mix together. Add the @British beef mince{240%g} and half of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}. Season with @pepper{}. Using your hands, mix everything together until very well combined. Form the mixture into evenly sized balls, 4 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the meatballs and fry until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Drain and discard any excess fat from the meatballs. Pour in the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1}, @chicken stock paste{10%g} and half of the @Italian style herbs{1/2%tsp}. Stir together well, cover with a #lid{} or #foil{}, reduce the heat and simmer until the meatballs are cooked, ~{6-7%minutes}.

Meanwhile, cut the @ciabatta{1} in half. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Pop the garlic into a #small bowl{}, along with the remaining @Italian style herbs{1/2%tsp} and the @olive oil{2%tbsp} for the garlic bread. Mix well to combine then spoon over the cut sides of the ciabatta. In another medium bowl, add the @cider vinegar{15%ml} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix well and leave to one side. This is your salad dressing.

After your meatballs have simmered for 6-7 mins, remove the lid and continue to simmer gently until the sauce has thickened, a further ~{3-4%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Then take off the heat and transfer to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g} and sprinkle it over, along with the remaining @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Pop the meatball parmigiana onto the top shelf of your oven and bake until the cheese has melted and is bubbling, ~{5-6%minutes}. At the same time, lay your garlic bread onto a #baking tray{} and put on the middle shelf to bake, until crisp and golden, ~{5-6%minutes}. While the meatball parmigiana and garlic bread bake, trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} then separate the leaves. Add the leaves to the dressing bowl and mix well to coat.

Once the meatball parmigiana and garlic bread are ready, remove them from the oven. Spoon the cheesy meatballs onto your plates and serve with the garlic bread and dressed baby gem salad alongside. Mama Mia! Enjoy.